  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, <strong>garlic</strong> and<strong> ginger</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 6-8 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pollock-pathia-with-turmeric-rice-and-naan/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a pot with a matching lid with a generous drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>cumin seeds</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until sizzling</p><p>Once the cumin seeds start to sizzle, carefully add the <strong>basmati rice</strong> and stir it all together</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pollock-pathia-with-turmeric-rice-and-naan/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong> and 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to the pot and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving – this is your <strong>turmeric rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pollock-pathia-with-turmeric-rice-and-naan/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, boil half a kettle</p><p>Chop the<strong> pollock fillets</strong> into large, bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pollock-pathia-with-turmeric-rice-and-naan/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the<strong> chopped ginger</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> to the pan and cook for 1-2 min further or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>ground cumin</strong>,<strong> curry powder</strong> and <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with the <strong>tomato paste</strong> and stir it all together</p><p>Tip: Add a drizzle of oil if the pan looks a little dry</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pollock-pathia-with-turmeric-rice-and-naan/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> tamarind paste </strong>with 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until the sauce is beginning to thicken</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped pollock </strong>and cook for 3-4 min further or until the fish is cooked through – this is your <strong>pollock pathia</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pollock-pathia-with-turmeric-rice-and-naan/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the fish is almost cooked, add the <strong>mini</strong> <strong>garlic & coriander naans </strong>to a baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 3 min or until the naans are warm</p><p>Tip: For a little extra indulgence, butter the hot naans once they are out of the oven</p><p>Meanwhile, chop the<strong> coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pollock-pathia-with-turmeric-rice-and-naan/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> pollock pathia</strong> with the<strong> turmeric rice</strong> and <strong>warmed naans</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the<strong> chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
